deck: Rowa is the Atlantean Elder of Science and a member of the Atlantean council.
description:
Current Events

Rowa is the Atlantean Elder of Science and a member of the Atlantean council. She serves king Aquaman.

She was the one who discovered a threat to the word's oceans related to Swamp Thing and brought it to the attention of the Atlantean council

Creation

Rowa was created by Aquaman writer Jeff Parker and artist Paul Pelletier. She made her debut in Aquaman #29.

Powers & Abilities

Rowa is an Atlantean and possesses their typical superhuman abilities.

Superhuman Strength

Rowa like all Atlanteans has some degree of superhuman strength.

Enhanced Durability

Rowa like all Atlanteans has some degree of enhanced durability.

Underwater Adaptation

She can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep.

Intellect (Science)

She is the Elder of Science and the chief scientist of Atlantis.

description:
Current Events

Kae is the Atlantean Seneschal and a member of the Atlantean council. He serves king Aquaman. He is a royal officer in charge of administrative duties in Atlantis as well as monitoring any surface or aquatic threats to the world. He has extensive knowledge of everything concerning Atlantis.

Creation

Kae was created by Aquaman writer Jeff Parker and artist Paul Pelletier. He made his debut in Aquaman#26.

Powers & Abilities

Kae is an Atlantean and possesses their typical superhuman abilities.

Superhuman Strength

Kae like all Atlanteans has some degree of superhuman strength.

Enhanced Durability

Kae like all Atlanteans has some degree of enhanced durability.

Underwater Adaptation

He can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep.

Intellect (Administrative Duties and Atlantean History)

He is the Seneschal of Atlantis and an expert on administrative duties and monitoring the day to day operations of Atlantis and the Atlantean Council. He also has extended knowledge of Atlantean history.

deck: A coward dies a thousand times before his death, but the valiant taste of death but once.
description:
Origin

During the Invasion of Poland at the start of World War II John Kowalski dies a coward when he could have helped many others. As punishment for this Death puts a curse on him that causes his spirit to travel the world and possess other people just before they are about to die. Death however gives him a way to redeem himself, if he can help those around the body he is possessing, saving those who are about to die before their time, and making things better for others he will eventually be released from his curse

Then they told the authorities that it was Rocky, who shot the security guard.

Rocky was sent to slammer for 20 years.

When Rocky was freed, another rock collided with the poor saps head, and then memories came back. The horrid memories.

Rocky swore vengeance.

Managed to kill two people, but Batman and Robin saved two others.

At the end of the story, Rocky died.
